ideo, has accused the Team GB star of beating the animal more than 24 times in a minute.\", \"from\": 4509, \"to\": 4661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4509, \"end\": 4516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eline_Heger\", \"score\": 0.9710441614875185, \"rank\": 0.029787258033542575, \"text\": \"Stephan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eline_Heger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eline_Heger\"}, {\"begin\": 4595, \"end\": 4602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999862821691325, \"rank\": 1.3105562837877883e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympics: Charlotte Dujardin is currently in the spotlight after being forced to withdraw from the Paris games  GETTY  Durjardin has already apologised for her actions, with the veteran saying: \\\"A video has emerged from four years ago which shows me making an error of judgement during a coaching session.\", \"from\": 4663, \"to\": 4968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4673, \"end\": 4691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Dujardin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\"}, {\"begin\": 4762, \"end\": 4767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999608917, \"rank\": 3.901242312674502e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Understandably, the International Federation for Equestrian Sports (FEI) is investigating and I have made the decision to withdraw from all competition - including the Paris Olympics - while this process takes place.\", \